to the library team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 2238437210, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMjM4NDM3MjEw", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-io", "name": "A-io", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: std::io, std::fs, std::net and std::path"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2021-12-02T10:09:22Z", "updated_at": "2022-04-08T10:13:52Z", "closed_at": "2022-04-08T10:13:52Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Apologies if this has been covered before. I've searched the bug tracker but didn't find an exact match.\r\n\r\n`net::Ipv6Addr::is_loopback()` returns true for `::1` and false for everything else.\r\n\r\nI would have expected it to return true for `fe80::1` (or strict: `fe80::1%lo0`) because, while a link-local address,  it's restricted to the loopback interface.\r\n\r\nSupporting evidence:\r\n```\r\n$ ifconfig lo0\r\nlo0: flags=8049<UP,LOOPBACK,RUNNING,MULTICAST> mtu 16384\r\n        options=1203<RXCSUM,TXCSUM,TXSTATUS,SW_TIMESTAMP>\r\n        inet 127.0.0.1 netmask 0xff000000 \r\n        inet6 ::1 prefixlen 128 \r\n        inet6 fe80::1%lo0 prefixlen 64 scopeid 0x1 <-- HERE \r\n        nd6 options=201<PERFORMNUD,DAD>\r\n```\r\nA more principled approach perhaps is a hypothetical `SocketAddrV6::is_loopback()` method that returns true when the scope id refers to a loopback device.\r\n\r\nBackground: libstd and getifaddrs(3) disagree on what is and isn't a local address, which is somewhat jarring.", "closed_by": {"login": "bnoordhuis", "id": 275871, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI3NTg3MQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/275871?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis", "html_url": "https://github.com/bnoordhuis", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bnoordhuis/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/u